Question: How to get the last element of a List in Java?
Please using this api: List.get.
Answer:<<<api>>>: List.get
<<<code>>>: List<String> list = new ArrayList<String>();
list.add("One");
list.add("Two");
list.add("Three");
String lastElement = list.get(list.size() - 1);
<<<explanation>>>: The get() method of the List interface returns the element at the specified position in this list. The size() method of the List interface returns the number of elements in this list. So, to get the last element, we use size() - 1 as the index.
